# ESLify Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your values.

```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
```

## Supabase

Get these from your [Supabase project settings](https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api).

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
```

## OpenRouter

Get your API key from [OpenRouter](https://openrouter.ai/keys).

**Important:** Rotate your key if it was ever exposed in client-side code.

```
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...
```

## Stripe

Get these from your [Stripe Dashboard](https://dashboard.stripe.com/).

1. Create product **ESLify Pro** with two prices:
   - Monthly: $15/month recurring
   - Yearly: $99/year recurring
2. Copy the Price IDs (start with `price_`)
3. Create a webhook endpoint pointing to `https://your-domain.vercel.app/api/stripe/webhook`
   - Events: `checkout.session.completed`, `customer.subscription.updated`, `customer.subscription.deleted`

```
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
STRIPE_PRICE_MONTHLY=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_YEARLY=price_...
```

## App URL

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

Use your production URL on Vercel (e.g. `https://eslify.vercel.app`).

## Supabase Auth Redirect URLs

In Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → URL Configuration, add:

- Site URL: `http://localhost:3000` (and production URL)
- Redirect URLs:
  - `http://localhost:3000/auth/callback`
  - `https://your-domain.vercel.app/auth/callback`

## Database Migration

Run the migration in `supabase/migrations/20250615000000_initial_schema.sql` via:

- Supabase Dashboard SQL Editor, or
- `supabase db push` if using the Supabase CLI
